title: For Sale/Trade:  H&R Topper 88 12 gauge - full choke
postcontent:
I have a used Harrington & Richardson Topper 88.  There is almost no rust on this gun, and there are just a few small marks in the wood.  Better than 90% of the original finish is still there.

The receiver is case hardened, so it has the beautiful colors.  This example really is exceptional as far as the coloring goes.  Serial number indicates it was manufactured in 1980, so it's a "real" Harrington & Richardson.  This shotgun is in much better shape than most of the shotguns you see in this price range.

It is a break action, single shot, 12 gauge, and it has a fixed full choke and a functional external hammer.  3" chamber.

Perfect for shooting trap, cowboy action & SASS, and it makes a great beginner shotgun.  Full choke also makes it a good turkey/bird gun.

Asking $125 O.B.O.  Please do NOT ask my "bottom dollar," as you will get the response "$125 O.B.O."

title: For Sale/Trade:  High Standard Sentinel "Snub" .22 revolver
postcontent:
This is a good old 9 shot, .22 LR DA revolver. The "Sentinel Snub" version is fairly scarce from what I have seen on some of the auction and HS sites, even more so with the factory bobbed hammer., so it has some interest to the High Standard crowd.

Shows wear and tear from being the knockaround gun for a few decades, original bakelite grips are in good shape, works DA or SA flawlessly, no ejection issues as long as you clean it once every 5 or 6 years, and the bore is great. The hammer is case hardened, that isn't rust you see there.

Just a nice old tin can shooter, these were incredibly well built, reliable "kit gun" revolvers, and it is an accurate little shooter as well, just right for the console of the truck, tackle box, or to just take for a walk in the woods. 9 Rounds of a good hot .22 wouldn't be the end of the world as far as a nightstand gun, too. 

I'm looking for $250 with a good little leather belt holster and a box of rounds. FTF, permit holders with supporting ID only, might think about a swap for this one.
